quoteFirst: The Court of _France_, tho’ very splendid by reason of the number of Princes and Princesses of which it consists, was nevertheless not so gay as I expected. The Life at _Versailles_ was the most uniform in the World: The King’s Hours were settled, and he that had seen but one Day there had seen a Year. The King rose at nine or
quoteLast: . The Princes and all the Courtiers attended his Levee, and after he was dress’d he kneel’d down to Prayers on a Cushion of Black Velvet, with his Chaplains and the Bishops that were at his Levee, kneeling also round him. When Prayers were ended, the King went into his Closet, where sometimes the Ministers came to speak to him about Business, and in the mean while the Courtiers walk’d in the great Gallery, thro’ which the King walk’d to hear Mass, and there all the Courtiers waited to be seen by his Majesty as he pass’d.
